Hey there.

Wanted to make my final update for this mod.

I am abandoning this mod. I have lost all interest in it and no longer find enjoyment in making it. I barely even play KSP as it is. School, friends, projects I'm working on, other hobbies I'm looking into, and many other things in life have come up at a higher priority and I don't find this as a fun way of getting away from it all. I don't even know where to take this, and don't update it for future versions as often as I should. I don't have time to work on it/don't enjoy it anymore.

HOWEVER! This does not mean the mod itself is abandoned. If anyone wants to take up the project, go ahead. Be sure to check in with Erona first and see if he's okay with not working on the project anymore. I'm just abandoning it, I have no clue if he wants to/ doesn't have time to and would rather hand it off. If you do though, give me and or Erona some "Original creator of pack" credit. I don't ask for much, just something simple to write. It was fun for the time I worked on it though, and will miss those fun times, but I'm moving on to new things. I'd rather not hold this pack back for no reason.

Be sure you actually can and want to take this up though, don't want this suffering the same fate again. Just send me a PM if you want to. I'll still lurk around the forums here but I won't be here very often. Good night, and good bye everyone!

Thanks for your hard work on such a great mod Thesonicgalaxy, really makes the Kerbin system a place of beauty

I hope someone continues the project
Thank you for your hard work on this mod, for releasing it to a successor, and for announcing your departure from the project

Not development-related, but have a very pretty pic, thanks to your mod.

This is my Minmus mission Challenger 3.

TECHNICALLY, I'm up and ready to go to land a Kerbal on Duna...there's just one problem.

Since I take KSP way too seriously, I need a biome to land on. It's critical. So I am stuck replaying my space program up to the point I am "currently" at until 0.90. (So excited!)

This is my Minmus campaign, I call it The Challenger Program.

I even made a custom flag for it that I edited out of the ASTP (Apollo-Soyuz Test Project, 1975) patch. I think I did a fair job.

Anywho, I landed in the crud, in the dark. (close call), timewarped, and began EVA 1 of the Challenger 3 mission.

Lo and behold, Kerbin and Mun were ever so picturesque behind me. God it was a beautiful sight.

Breathtaking mod - the clouds on Minmus are cool, but i'm thinking of getting rid of that layer in the ALT-N GUI - a fantastic feature.

Thanks!

*EDIT* - no, my Mun lander is not what you see here (The FASA LEM), it's a custom stock 2-stage vehicle, I just got lazy when it came to Minmus. At least the rocket was different. (I hate using the same rocket for everything, got to diversify!)

**** Crash! ****

When I had just EVE and custom Asteroids downloaded, the game worked fine. However, downloading this and the other mods causes the game to crash right as it begins to load the menu screen, which sucks because I have to spend 10 minutes waiting for all my mods to load. Not sure which error file to show, so I'll just show the end of the output log:

I'm no expert, but I noticed this at the top of your log:

Could not allocate memory: System out of memory!

This might indicate that you are using all of the memory available to KSP. This is a known limitation for adding mods to KSP, primarily for the 32-bit version of KSP. Eventually, there should be a stable 64-bit version of KSP, which will allow the use of many more mods. For now, you probably have to choose which mods are the most important for you. Also, you might look at a mod such as Active Texture Mangement.

In any case, I'm betting it's not a Better-Atmospheres-specific issue.

I agree with Gryphon.

Installing this package did spike my memory as well so one of the needed mods is doing something behind the scenes. I had to switch to Aggressive (Instead of Basic) Active Texture Manager & go into my game settings and change the texture res to "Half Rez". That took about 1gb out of my memory footprint and everything except the Toolbar mod icons I use for a cpl of my mods still look beautiful

This fixed my Toolbar icons so it worked out in the end:
